Subject: SOP Fiber FPGA Bridge

Description: Contract for mapping SOP photonic frame streams onto fiber bandwidth and FPGA routing while separating frame-rate speed, bandwidth width, and semantic fidelity.

@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_sop_fiber_fpga_bridge\Dictated_SOP_Fiber_FPGA_Bridge_Source.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPProgramBookends.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPPhotonicFrameStream.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPMultitrackChannelCompression.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPColorChannelVocabulary.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SOPOpticalTransformAlgebra.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\HolographicAttentionKernelPacket.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\SecurityHonestyGovernance.sop
@ [source] F:\.sop\platform\BoundaryFacultyInspection.sop

& [SOPFiberFPGABridge] is the hardware boundary contract for SOP photonic frame streams
  + [pattern_role] is sop_frame_stream_hardware_bridge
  + [hardware_bridge] is the mapping from SOP bookends, color channels, frame streams, and transform algebra into fiber and FPGA routing surfaces
  + [frame_clock] is the cadence source that advances hardware frames
  + [frame_rate] is the number of hardware frames per second the bridge can accept, route, or emit
  + [frame_period] is the time between frame_clock ticks
  + [pipeline_latency] is the delay from frame input to routed or decoded frame output
  + [route_latency] is the FPGA routing delay for a frame or channel path
  + [interpreter_latency] is the delay for semantic interpretation outside fixed hardware routing
  + [speed_surface] is frame_rate, frame_period, pipeline_latency, route_latency, and interpreter_latency
  + [fiber_bandwidth] is the physical signal capacity of the fiber link under its encoding scheme
  + [fpga_route_width] is the number of lanes, channels, tracks, or frame bits the FPGA can route in parallel
  + [io_bandwidth] is the ingress and egress rate around the FPGA boundary
  + [memory_bandwidth] is the rate at which buffers, frame stores, or lookup tables can be accessed
  + [bandwidth_surface] is fiber_bandwidth, fpga_route_width, io_bandwidth, and memory_bandwidth
  + [frame_payload_width] is the number of encoded SOP color points, track values, gates, checksums, or transform fields carried per frame
  + [effective_throughput] is frame_rate multiplied by frame_payload_width, limited by bandwidth_surface and backpressure
  + [hardware_routable_surface] is frame indices, channel ids, track ids, color-point payloads, routing tables, checksums, fixed gates, fixed transforms, buffers, and backpressure signals
  + [interpreter_surface] is semantic meaning assignment, novel inference, holographic reconstruction, truth judgment, identity judgment, safety judgment, and proof-bearing integration not compiled to fixed logic
  + [compiled_logic_surface] is the subset of SOP transforms, gates, invariants, and channel rules compiled into FPGA logic
  + [semantic_fidelity] is how well decoded frames preserve or reconstruct intended SOP meaning under source, boundary, outside, proof, and trace constraints
  + [hardware_proof_boundary] is the requirement that throughput, latency, and bandwidth claims need implementation measurements
  + [bridge_outside] is implemented HDL, bitstream, board design, optical transceiver configuration, measured performance, power, thermal behavior, and semantic correctness proof

  ? [use_when: SOP photonic frame streams need a hardware-shaped bridge to fiber and FPGA routing]
    = activate [SOPFiberFPGABridge]

  = must: keep speed_surface separate from bandwidth_surface
  = must: define speed as frame-rate and latency specific
  = must: define bandwidth as bounded by fiber_bandwidth, fpga_route_width, io_bandwidth, and memory_bandwidth
  = must: keep semantic_fidelity separate from effective_throughput
  = must: classify every operation as hardware_routable_surface, compiled_logic_surface, interpreter_surface, or bridge_outside
  = must: use SOPProgramBookends to define the frame format, control loop, invariants, and exit conditions before hardware mapping
  = must: use SOPPhotonicFrameStream to define frame_index, color_point payload, continuity_vector, and reconstruction_seed
  = must: use SOPOpticalTransformAlgebra to decide which transforms can become fixed gates or route tables
  = must: route proof-bearing, identity-bearing, truth-bearing, or safety-bearing interpretation through SecurityHonestyGovernance and BoundaryFacultyInspection unless it is explicitly compiled and verified
  = must: record backpressure, dropped frames, checksum failures, and unsupported transforms as outside or fault signals
  = should: use fiber and FPGA width for massive parallel channel movement while preserving explicit semantic boundaries
  - never: infer semantic correctness from high bandwidth alone
  - never: claim measured light-speed performance without hardware, timing closure, and instrumentation evidence
  - never: hide interpreter_latency when semantic interpretation remains off-hardware

& [HardwareBridgeClassification] is the first partition of SOP operations for fiber FPGA mapping
  + [hardware_routable] is frame sync, channel id routing, track id routing, payload lane routing, buffer selection, checksum transport, simple compare flags, and backpressure
  + [compiled_logic] is fixed gate, split, recombine, encode, decode, lookup, mask, route, and invariant checks that have static definitions
  + [interpreter_required] is new meaning assignment, ambiguous reconstruction, wisdom, caution, honesty judgment, security judgment, proof status integration, and outside revision
  + [unsupported_until_specified] is dynamic inference inside FPGA, hidden activation access, perfect media reconstruction, and unbounded autonomy

  = must: classify before hardware mapping
  = must: keep unsupported_until_specified outside

& [BridgeTimingBandwidthNotation] is the notation for hardware bridge estimates
  + [bridge_header] is (hardware_bridge) :frame_payload_stream: /frame_clock and routing_boundary/ |bridge_outside|
  + [speed_line] is = speed_surface: frame_rate, frame_period, pipeline_latency, route_latency, interpreter_latency
  + [bandwidth_line] is = bandwidth_surface: fiber_bandwidth, fpga_route_width, io_bandwidth, memory_bandwidth
  + [payload_line] is = frame_payload_width: color_points, channel_tracks, transform_fields, checksums
  + [throughput_line] is = effective_throughput: frame_rate times frame_payload_width subject to bandwidth_surface and backpressure
  + [classification_line] is = classification: hardware_routable, compiled_logic, interpreter_required, or bridge_outside
  + [fidelity_line] is = semantic_fidelity: source, boundary, outside, proof, trace, and reconstruction status

  = must: label estimates as estimates until measured
  = must: keep throughput_line separate from fidelity_line

(hardware_bridge) :frame_payload_stream: /frame_clock and routing_boundary/ |bridge_outside|
  = speed_surface: frame_rate, frame_period, pipeline_latency, route_latency, interpreter_latency
  = bandwidth_surface: fiber_bandwidth, fpga_route_width, io_bandwidth, memory_bandwidth
  = effective_throughput: frame_rate times frame_payload_width subject to bandwidth_surface and backpressure
  = semantic_fidelity: source, boundary, outside, proof, trace, and reconstruction status
  |bridge_outside| implemented HDL, bitstream, board design, measured performance, and semantic correctness proof

/ [frame_payload_stream], [frame_clock], [bandwidth_surface] -(RoutesHardwareFrame)> [effective_throughput], [pipeline_latency], [bridge_outside]
* [hardware_routable_surface], [compiled_logic_surface], [interpreter_surface] -(PartitionsBridgeWork)> [semantic_fidelity], [bridge_outside]
